cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with video object segmentation using deep nets, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves learning to match extracted features to a provided template, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of deep nets for prediction tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The datasets used in the experiments are related to multimedia (cs.MM), and the proposed method is designed to be more favorable in terms of computational time, which is a common concern in robotics (cs.RO).
